parties.raw_snippet:
This TRADEMARK LICENSE AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is effective as of the [·] day of [·], 2019 (“Effective Date”) between
Morgan Stanley Investment Management Inc. (“Licensor”), and Morgan Stanley Direct Lending Fund, a Delaware corporation (“Licensee”).
parties.reasoning: The opening paragraph explicitly names the contracting parties and identifies their roles (Licensor and Licensee). These are the primary parties to the agreement.

contract_type.reasoning: The document title at the top identifies the type of contract as a license agreement concerning a trademark.

notice_period.reasoning: The agreement contains no clause requiring advance notice to prevent an automatic renewal. Instead, Section 4.1 states the term continues "in perpetuity," so there is no renewal-notice-to-prevent-auto-renewal requirement to extract.

expiration_date.raw_snippet: Section 4.1.Term. The term of this Agreement commences on the Effective Date and continues in perpetuity, unless termination occurs pursuant to Sections 4.2 through 4.4.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 4.1 explicitly states the agreement "continues in perpetuity," which is explicit language supporting a perpetual term.

renewal_term.reasoning: No renewal or automatic renewal term language appears in the agreement; the term is stated as continuing in perpetuity and there is no renewal-period provision to extract.
